    Name=3; Synonyms=Alpha;
      IsoId=Q7Z2W7-3; Sequence=VSP_012330, VSP_012332, VSP_012333;
-!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Expressed in prostate. Also expressed in most
    in prostate tumors. Also expressed in non-prostatic primary tumors
    such as colon, lung, breast and skin tumors.
-!- MISCELLANEOUS: The sensation of coolness triggered by eucalyptol
    or menthol may be explained by the fact that menthol and cool
    temperatures sensations are detected by this protein.
-!- MISCELLANEOUS: Its expression in most prostate tumors as well as
    the presence of an immunogenic epitope suggest that it may be
    suitable for the design of peptide vaccination strategies for
    prostate cancers.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the transient receptor family. LTrpC
    subfamily.
